The paper deals with trajectory indexing and similarity search, which are common problems in database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of fingerprinting and sharded inverted indexes also suggests a focus on efficient data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the importance of privacy and security in trajectory data, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed method, which could be relevant to distributed systems (cs.SI).
